Everton have confirmed that Duncan Ferguson, will take charge of the team, for Sunday’s trip to Manchester United. Ferguson stepped in after Marco Silva was sacked last week and led the Toffees to a shock 3-1 win over Chelsea on Saturday. He will now remain in the dugout for the game at Old Trafford, with coaches John Ebbrell and Francis Jeffers continuing assist along with goalkeeper coach Alan Kelly. “Duncan Ferguson will remain as Everton caretaker manager for Sunday’s Premier League visit to Manchester United. “Former striker Ferguson was in charge as the Blues secured a 3-1 victory over Chelsea at Goodison on Saturday. “Ferguson will again be assisted by coaches John Ebbrell and Francis Jeffers and goalkeeper coach Alan Kelly,” a club statement read. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.